reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars 10 month old loves this toy
reviews.reviewText: My 10 month old grandson loves anything with a cord. We are constantly on guard to catch him with the closest iphone or ipad cord, electrical cords, etc. Not sure what the fascination is, but this toy helps to redirect his interest. It has multiple cords going through a base. You can pull the cord all the way through to one side, flip it over and pull it back through again. He tends to chew on it as well. My husband has even used one of the cords on it to tie onto his walker so he has it handy to play with. We actually have 3 of these so one is always available.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Got it for 6 month old
reviews.reviewText: I was looking for a toy for my baby that loves to grab and pull on cords and anything string like. This was the only toy I found with that idea so I gave it a shot. He really does like it. The middle round piece is hard plastic and slightly heavy, so with a young baby it would likely hurt if they hit themselves with it. I think that’s why it’s recommended for 18 months. So I try to keep an eye on him when he’s playing with it. But other than that, it’s great and works for his age just fine. I think it’s a toy that will be played for a couple of years hopefully!
